to split(someText, delimiter) set AppleScript's text item delimiters to delimiter set someText to someText's text items set AppleScript's text item delimiters to {""} return someText end split
on run argv --Set string content variables via shell script, as AppleScript in Alfred, referencing environment variables directly, does not support UTF8 set draftContent to do shell script "echo " & quoted form of (system attribute "content") & " | iconv -f UTF-8-MAC -t MACROMAN" set draftTagsString to do shell script "echo " & quoted form of (system attribute "tags") & " | iconv -f UTF-8-MAC -t MACROMAN" set draftFlagged to (system attribute "flagged") set draftTags to split(draftTagsString, ",")
tell application "Drafts" return make new draft with properties {content: draftContent, flagged: draftFlagged, tags: draftTags} end tell end run
on run argv set theQuery to item 1 of argv do shell script "open -a '" & (POSIX path of theQuery) & "'" -- In case we want to debug... return "open -a '" & (POSIX path of theQuery) & "'" end run

# Output true if we have a specific UUID specified
if (( ${+UUID} )); then echo -n UUID else echo -n MATCH fi
on run argv tell application "System Events" tell (first process whose frontmost is true) set appPath to ((path to frontmost application) as text) end tell end tell return appPath end run

#Initialise variables DV=$(defaults read "/Applications/Drafts.app/Contents/Info" CFBundleVersion) PN=$(sw_vers -productName) PV=$(sw_vers -productVersion) BV=$(sw_vers -buildVersion) cp "$HOME/Library/Group Containers/GTFQ98J4YG.com.agiletortoise.Drafts/Library/Preferences/GTFQ98J4YG.com.agiletortoise.Drafts.plist" "$HOME/doctorDrafts-Drafts.plist" SID=$(defaults read "$HOME/doctorDrafts-Drafts" com.agiletortoise.SubscriptionManager.Identifier) EXP=$(defaults read "$HOME/doctorDrafts-Drafts" com.agiletortoise.SubscriptionManager.ExpirationDate) EXPDTLEN=$(echo -n $EXP | wc -m) if [[ EXPDTLEN != 0 ]] then BETA=" *" else BETA="" fi rm "$HOME/doctorDrafts-Drafts.plist"
#Output body for e-mail message echo --- echo "Drafts Version: $DV$BETA" echo "OS Version: $PN, $PV ($BV)" echo $SID echo --- echo
